<p class="GeneralText mb-2">A “cookie” is a small piece of information stored by a web server on a web browser so it can be later read back from that browser. Cookies are useful for enabling the browser to remember information specific to a given user. We place both permanent and temporary cookies in your computer’s hard drive. The cookies do not contain any of your personally identifiable information. Except as required under applicable law, all personal information which is collected by us will only be retained by us for the duration necessary to fulfill the requests or purposes for which such personal information was disclosed to us including but not limited to until such time that your User Account continues to subsist with us.</p>
